 Legal Authorities Primary authority A primary authority is a term used in legal research to refer to statements of law that are binding upon the courts, government, and individuals. Primary authority is usually in the form of a document that establishes the law, and if no document exists, is a legal opinion of a court. The search for applicable primary authority is the most important part of the process of legal research. Examples of primary authority include the verbatim tex⋯⋯ts of : -Constitutions -Basic laws -Statutes (whether codified or un-codified) -Treaties and certain other international law materials -Municipal charters and ordinances -Court opinions -Rules of court procedure -Rules of evidence -Rules governing the conduct of lawyers -Administrative regulations -Executive orders Secondary authority In law, a secondary authority is an authority purporting to explain the meaning or applicability of the actual verbatim texts of primary authorities (such as constitutions, statutes, case law, administrative regulations, executive orders, treaties, or similar legal instruments). Some secondary authority materials are written and published by governments to explain the laws in simple, non-technical terms, while other secondary authority materials are written and published by private companies, non-profit organizations, or other groups or individuals. Some examples of secondary authority are : -Law review articles, comments and notes (written by law professors, practicing lawyers, law students, etc.) -Legal textbooks, such as legal treatises and hornbooks -Legal digests, such as the West American Digest System -Annotations published in statute books, codes, or other materials, such as the annotations in the American Law Reports series -Legal encyclopedias (such as Corpus Juris Secundum Encyclopedia of Law and American Jurisprudence) -Legal dictionaries (such as Black's Law Dictionary) -Restatements of the Law published by the American Law Institute -Legal briefs and memoranda; -Tax forms and instructions published by governments -Government publications explaining or summarizing the laws -Government employee manuals (such as the Internal Revenue Manual for employees of the Internal Revenue Service) -Course materials from continuing legal education seminars Debate in legislatures, including such commentaries published in the Congressional Record (this may reveal legislative intent) -Other similar materials In the United States, various legal scholars disagree over whether legislative histories in the form of texts of congressional committee reports should be considered to be secondary authority or, alternatively, primary authority. 更多72小時搞懂英美法導讀 · 2015年10月8日 · (插播) 課程公告 英美法導讀 10/17正常上課 10/24停課乙次⋯⋯ 補課方式 請同學自行上網報名前往圖書館 http://www.library.scu.edu.tw/Page/168 10/17或10/30 WestlawNext法律資料庫或Lexis.com法律資料庫講習 任何一場即可 謝謝配合 更多2015_城區分館資料庫講習 | 東吳大學圖書館ø專業資料庫講習課程，歡迎以班級為單位報名參加 ，上課時間可另外安排，請洽賴秋惠(分機2442)library.scu.edu.tw72小時搞懂英美法導讀 · 2015年9月26日 · What is the Common Law? This lecture can help you realize the history and development of the common law.  Please go through it and make your own notes.Lecture 1 Part 2 : What is the Common Law?Dame Hazel Genn discusses the history and development of the common lawyoutube.com72小時搞懂英美法導讀 · 2015年9月23日 · 請各位同學思考下列各項對於Common Law常見的解釋是否完全正確?有何偏頗之處? Common Law就是指英美法 Common Law是指不成文法 Common Law又可稱為Case Law或判例法⋯⋯ Common Law是習慣法 那麼 若將Common Law翻譯成普通法呢? (以下開放留言回答) 更多72小時搞懂英美法導讀 · 2015年9月22日 · 學法律的第一堂課 讀法律系的目的=> 學習如何用法律摧毀別人的自尊, 或如何被別人用法律摧毀自尊!⋯⋯ ( 找一天上課, 來模仿一下劇中的教授^^) 更多The Paper Chase (1973)youtube.com72小時搞懂英美法導讀 · 2015年9月18日 · First Step:  Tell the difference between civil law and common law. Ask yourself: - what the common law is and ⋯⋯ - why it is common. 更多1 7 Legal Traditions The civil law and the common law 15 10youtube.com查看更多
































